page.title: 16Housing-N.W.Bury St.Edmunds
page.content: Most of the houses in the area have been built since 1960. The majority are council-built, but there is a mixture of private and municipal dwellings. The former are varied, bungalows, chalets and two-storey styles all being represented. The latter are small two and three bedroomed houses, semi-detached or in short terraces. There is a great variety of style and several kinds of brick and cladding are used. Garages are in separate blocks and the small gardens are open-plan at the front. There are several squares and open spaces, which with the grass verges and tree-lined roads create a very pleasant environment, and it is not surprising that some houses have been bought by tenants. Along the main roads are a few large older houses in big gardens.
